ari/537.36", "Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format_id": "4", "format": "4 - 750x1333"}], "title": "Video by soulfulsongs77", "description": "The way he stopped playing guitar just to hear them sing was priceless✨\n\n“More Than Words” by Extreme was released in 1990 as the third single from their second studio album Pornograffitti. The song became the band’s biggest commercial success, reaching top hit and gaining worldwide popularity for its stripped-down acoustic style, which contrasted sharply with the band’s usual hard rock sound. \n\nMusically, the track is built around gentle acoustic guitar fingerpicking by Nuno Bettencourt and soft, intimate vocals from Gary Cherone, creating a minimalist arrangement that places emotional emphasis on the message. \n\nLyrically, the song explores the idea that saying “I love you” is not enough without meaningful actions to support those words; it challenges superficial expressions of love and calls for sincerity and commitment. \n\nIts heartfelt delivery and simplicity helped it become one of the most recognizable acoustic ballads of the early 1990s\n\ndm for credits or removal \n\n[ music, 90s, more than words, extreme, acoustic, guitar, live, reaction, crowd, pop music ]", "duration": 39.638, "timestamp": 1774494089, "uploader_id": "40879562062", "uploader": "Soulfulsongs", "channel": "soulfulsongs77", "like_count": 87642, "comment_count": 812, "comments": [{"author": "popppyfield", "author_id": "2383623263", "id": "18097209457837837", "text": "@stooch39  chuuune 🎶", "timestamp": 1775171029}, {"author": "kerrylbs", "author_id": "231171918", "id": "18118785559716575", "text": "Love this 🔥", "timestamp": 1775170762}, {"author": "x_._sienna_._x", "author_id": "228245448", "id": "18087544940195615", "text": "He’s as gorgeous as the song!! ♥️", "timestamp": 1775170477}, {"auth